So phenomenal. . I can't say enough good things about this creamy lemony risotto. I made it as directed, but held off on the last tablespoon or so of butter and added extra lemon juice instead. Wow, is it good. It's perfect alone for a cold night, but would also be great with the Parmesan Crusted Chicken.

Rating: 4
This was incredible. The lemon flavor is just this side of intense--you get the zinginess, but it doesn't besiege your gustatory senses. Rich and light, I reduced the butter and oil to 1 teaspoon each--with the broth and cheese more is not necessary. I also upped the wine to 1/2 cup and reduced the broth to 5 cups. Sumptuous.

Rating: 4
I doubled the recipe for a dinner for 10. Everyone loved it! The creamy consistency, lemony flavor, and hint of cheesiness were perfectly balanced together. It accompanied another recipe on this Web site, Pork Medallions w/ Mustard Cream Sauce (which I also highly recommend). This risotto is comfort food at its best. I'll certainly make it again.

