Rating: 4
This is the best risotto I've ever made. My spouse thought it too lemony (but still liked it) but I did not, I thought it had a very delicate lemon flavor and complimented the strong flavors of the proscuitto wrapped grilled shrimp and salad with gorgonzola and roasted garlic bread we had with it. Only changes: I used 7.5 cups of homemade onion stock as I don't like chicken broth and it took about an hour not 35 minutes. I used chopped fresh flat leaf parsley and I think I'll double the amount next time. I highly recommend this recipe.

