Rating: 4
Delicious, delicate taste, and perfect when you're puttering about the kitchen anyway, as you have to stick around to add broth and stir. I, too, halved the cheese, and kept the olive oil and butter to one tablespoon each (watching our weight here!). My one error: I had chicken bouillon cubes in the house and used them in place of the low-salt canned broth, so the resulting dish was a bit too salty. It made quite a large pan of risotto, but there's none left, so that says something about how good it was!

