Rating: 3
I have made a similar version of this dish which calls for stirring in the lemon zest after the first 15 minutes of cooking, as well as proportionally more lemon juice, and I find that this one is far mellower. My other recipe also includes minced sage, which adds a nice touch. Definitely, chicken broth better complements the lemon, as opposed to vegetable broth. A very good dish -- and lovely suggestion from the Pleasanton cook, who added asparagus. I have served this with roasted asparagus and it's an excellent choice. A little crostini, a dry white, a crisp salad = an elegant, simple summer meal!

